        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 2:15PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 215 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northwest of Broken Bow, or 35 miles west of De Queen, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wright City, Mount Herman, Sherwood, Bethel, Hochatown and Glover.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
